---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'

import portrait from '~/assets/speakers/ross-tuck.jpg'
import location from '~/assets/location.jpg'

import Layout from '~/layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Layout>
  <div class="banner" style={{ backgroundImage: `url(${location.src})` }}>
    <p>
      Ross Tuck<br />
      Freelance developer, consultant and speaker
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="copy" id="two-column">
    <div class="column" id="fullwidth">
      <h1 id="abstract">Everything is Anything: The Unlikely Wisdom of Historical Stabbings</h1>

      <p>
        This is not a talk about stabbing people. Violence is bad. But it is a talk about two people who tried to stab each other hundreds of years ago. It's also a talk about getting inspiration from unlikely sources â€” about how skills might not be transferable, but mastering a skill could be. About how, when the chips are down, anything can be everything.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="column" id="biography">
      <h1>About Ross</h1>
      <p>
        Ross Tuck is a freelance developer, consultant, and speaker. He lives in Utrecht and co-organizes DomCode, a cross-language user group. Tweet him at <code>@rosstuck</code>.
      </p>

      <p>
        <code>
          <a href="http://rosstuck.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://rosstuck.com/</a>
        </code>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="column" id="photograph">
      <Image src={portrait} alt="Ross Tuck" class="photograph" />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
